Problem Statement

A company ABC has N employees.
It has one office on each floor and in each office works one employee.
Each employee i works on the ith floor and has skill A[i].
Each employee can belong to at most one team.
Each team should have employees working in consecutive floors from i to j (a contiguous subarray). 
ABC uses a metric called the "expert number" which is calculated as the sum of all the "absent expert values" from each team.
The "absent expert value" of a team is the first skill starting from 0 which is not present in the team (this is mathematically known as the MEX - Minimum Excluded value).
You need to divide the employees into teams such that the company’s expert number is as large as possible.
Find the maximum expert number that can be obtained.

Constraints
1 <= N <= 10^5
0 <= A[i] <= 10^3

